<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   NITRO, W. Va. -- Heck's Inc. said shareholders approved
the previously announced sale of its retail division to
Retail Acquisition Corp. Terms weren't disclosed.
   The sale is expected to close in July, leaving the company
with its Steel City Products division, a wholesale
distributor of automotive parts and accessories based in
Pittsburgh. Shareholders also approved resolutions to change
the company's name to Hallwood Industries Inc. and its state
of incorporation to Delaware from West Virginia.
